            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

<script type='text/javascript'>
function showSpeciesNr(value, data)
{
    jQuery('#species_nr').val(data.species_nr);
    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }
    </script>
    <div id='quick-search-bar'>
        <form action='/explore' class='species-completion' method='post' autocomplete='off'>

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

                   <div id='xc_audio_290106_193' class='jp-type-single' data-xc-id='290106' data-xc-filepath='http://www.xeno-canto.org/sounds/uploaded/TYEQKORVXJ/XC290106-Pied%20Wagtail%20composition.mp3'>

        <td>
        <span class='common-name'><a href='/species/Motacilla-alba'>White Wagtail</a></span> (<span class='scientific-name'>Motacilla alba</span>)
        </td>
        <td>
        1:43
        </td>
        <td>
        <a href='/contributor/TYEQKORVXJ'>Anthony McGeehan </a>
        </td>
        
        <td>2015-09-27</td>
        <td> 19:00</td>
      
        <td>United Kingdom</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=54.6565&long=-5.6753&loc=Bangor%2C+North+Down%2C+Northern+Ireland">Bangor, North Down, Northern Ireland</a>
        </td>
        <td>30</td>
        <td>call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Rather than upload a series of clips, I have prepared a compilation of the sounds produced by Pied Wagtails [subspecies Motacilla alba yarrellii] as they settled into a roost. The location was a stand of four deciduous trees (around 8m in height) in a car park at a shopping mall. For at least the last two winters, up to 140 Pied Wagtails have used the trees until, sometime in late October, the foliage begins to fall and the birds move away (I do not know where they go). The edited clip splits into three roughly equal parts, each about 20 seconds long. In the first section, some birds have arrived and are calling (mainly) from the ground before flying up among the foliage. In the second clip, most have now arrived and many are calling in a kind of animated chorus (whilst I say 'many', I could not see any more than a handful of birds, most of which were now hidden). The third clip [begins at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(290106, 48);'>0:48</a>] is the most interesting. In it, you can hear the 'white noise' created by a number of birds bill-snapping. Once again, I do not know how many birds are doing this. Furthermore, I could not see any birds well enough to even observe the action. By then, it was dark. The bill snapping, in my estimation, is an expression of one bird effectively asserting proprietorial rights to its roosting perch. Once all the birds had settled down, the bill snapping ceased, although occasional calls still punctuated the air. The bill snapping is a curious sound. It suggests static or hailstones. You need to listen closely to hear it, even though it was coming like a crackling wave from every tree in the roost. It was as though most birds were contributing to the broadcast, not just a few. In the third clip bill snapping occurs constantly. It is best heard after a passing Herring Gull [<a onclick='xc.playFrom(290106, 80);'>1:20</a>] causes a bit of a lull in 'ordinary' chirping among the wagtails; in the brief absence of chirps, you can heard the bill snapping fairly clearly, for example at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(290106, 85);'>1:25</a> or at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(290106, 100);'>1:40</a>. Among the range of vocalisations produced by the wagtails, another aggressive-sounding call is quite like the hiss of a Goldfinch threatening another Goldfinch at, for example, a feeder. The Pied Wagtail equivalent is at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(290106, 72);'>1:12</a> and <a onclick='xc.playFrom(290106, 77);'>1:17</a>.  Bill snapping by Pied wagtails is mentioned in THE BIRDS OF THE WESTERN PALEARCTIC in vol. five, page 645. David W Emley also published a useful note on the subject in British Birds vol. 78 (1985), page 110.</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>
<p>   </p></div><a class='fancybox' rel='sono' href='http://www.xeno-canto.org/sounds/uploaded/TYEQKORVXJ/ffts/XC290106-large.png' title='XC290106: White Wagtail (Motacilla alba) by Anthony McGeehan '>[sono]</a></div></td>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Parte 4 de 4. La lavandera blanca es una especie invernante en esta zona de EspaÃ±a, llegando aquÃ­ en gran nÃºmero desde todos los puntos de Europa. Por la noche se reÃºnen en grandes dormideros comunales situados en grandes Ã¡rboles preferiblemente en ciudad y cerca de carreteras con gran trÃ¡fico, pues allÃ­ la temperatura es mÃ¡s alta y el nÃºmero de depredadores menor. Por el dÃ­a forrajean en grupos laxos en cualquier zona descubierta de parques, jardines, pastizales ralos y aledaÃ±os de marisma. En este songscape de lavandera blanca podemos oÃ­r grupos de la especie forrajeando en una de sus zonas favoritas, un pastizal pelado cerca de un humedal. Junto a ellas se oyen otras especies de fondo. La reserva es a la vez paraje protegido, lugar de explotaciÃ³n de ganado vacuno extensivo y coto de caza. No sÃ³lo sus usos son heterogÃ©neos, tambiÃ©n lo son sus ecosistemas: hay una laguna temporal irrigada por el arroyo majaberraque, una zona de pastizal abierto, un bosque de acebuches adehesados y un pinar con Ã¡rboles de gran envergadura. El suelo estÃ¡ muy desprovisto de vegetaciÃ³n por la gran carga ganadera de la zona, pero Ã©sto es fundamental para algunas especies que requieren Ã¡reas muy Ã¡ridas como Anthus Campestris, la bisbita campestre u Oenanthe Oennanthe, la collalba gris. Con todo es necesaria algo de regeneraciÃ³n vegetal y se han establecido pequeÃ±os cercaditos inaccesibles a las vacas para que en ellos crezcan acebuches nuevos y algo de hierba y matorral.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>

            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>

            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>

            </li>

            </li>

<span class='authority'>Gould, 1837</span></span></li></ul><h4>Unclassified</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/unspec-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">No subspecies specified</span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/bg-12.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">In background of another recording</span></li> </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>
            
            <h3>Map Legend</h3>
        
            <div class="map-legend">
                <h4>Subspecies</h4>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>

            <ul class='family'>

            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>

            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>

            </li>

            </li>

<span class='authority'>Meade-Waldo, 1901</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/l-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Motacilla-alba?query=ssp:%22yarrellii%22'>yarrellii</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>Gould, 1837</span></span></li></ul><h4>Unclassified</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/unspec-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">No subspecies specified</span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/bg-12.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text">In background of another recording</span></li> </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

<script type='text/javascript'>
function showSpeciesNr(value, data)
{
    jQuery('#species_nr').val(data.species_nr);
    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }
    </script>

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=46.9289&long=131.7158&loc=Fujin+Hei+Yupao+National+Wetlands+Park%2C+Heilongjiang">Fujin Hei Yupao National Wetlands Park, Heilongjiang</a>

        <td>call, male </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Same bird as <a href='/113660'>XC113660</a>. Based on range, this should be M. a. leucopsis, and it showed all the typical features of that subspecies - black back, black breast patch, extensive white forehead and face, but this particular male also had a narrow black eye-stripe, supposedly a feature of M. a. lugens.</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

<script type='text/javascript'>
function showSpeciesNr(value, data)
{
    jQuery('#species_nr').val(data.species_nr);
    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }
    </script>

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

<script type='text/javascript'>
function showSpeciesNr(value, data)
{
    jQuery('#species_nr').val(data.species_nr);
    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }
    </script>

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>White Wagtail &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Motacilla alba</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>Linnaeus, 1758</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Motacillidae'>Motacillidae</a> (Wagtails, Pipits)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Motacilla'>Motacilla</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>alba</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Motacilla_alba.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});
